{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "09", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "06", "M": "47", "S": "03"}}, "news": [{"title": "Haryana backs uniform nomenclature of lands in revenue records", "para": "Haryana is enhancing transparency in land administration by standardizing government land ownership entries in revenue records. Financial Commissioner Dr. Sumita Misra directed officials to uniformly record state government land as 'Haryana government' to eliminate ambiguity and improve governance. This reform ensures legal clarity and accountability in public land management.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/haryana-implements-standardization-in-land-records-to-enhance-transparency-and-governance/129303034?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-189628/129303034.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Paperless land surveys by end of year as services go online in Karnataka", "para": "The Survey, Settlement and Land Records wing is set to go fully digital by 2026. Citizens will soon apply for land surveys and get property documents online. This move aims to boost transparency and efficiency. Old records are being digitized. A unique land parcel identification number will be created for each property.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/karnatakas-revenue-department-to-go-fully-digital-by-2026-no-more-paperwork-for-land-surveys/129302682?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-64040/129302682.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}, {"title": "Land levelled, trees felled, road to new buildings laid at Damdama basin in Aravalis", "para": "Construction and a new road are altering the Damdama Lake catchment, a protected Aravali area. Land has been levelled and fenced, with electricity extended to new structures. This activity threatens Gurgaon's groundwater recharge system. Forest officials will inspect the site for violations. Environmental groups are calling for joint inspections and removal of unauthorised constructions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/land-destruction-and-road-construction-threaten-damdama-lakes-ecosystem/129302313?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-172408/129302313.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}